  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The project aims to test the effectiveness and explore the possibility of performing a novel
      therapeutic approach, targeting to increase strength and coordination around the trunk,
      giving a more active and functional seating and head control in those children with cerebral
      palsy (CP) who are wheelchair users. The project will also try to determine the muscle
      physiological effect of treatment using indirect measures of strength in the spinal
      musculature.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
